Former Mungiki leader Maina Njenga on Tuesday visited the Laikipia county assembly with his supporters to familiarise himself with House proceedings.Njenga, who has declared interest in running for Laikipia senator, was thoroughly screened by security officers at the entrance. During the proceedings in the afternoon session, he was seen following keenly contributions on the floor from his seat at the public gallery.Addressing the media after the session, Njenga applauded the House for its good work.He urged local leaders to stop unnecessary fights for the sake of the common mwananchi, saying conflicts are a hindrance to development.